      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must directly correspond to the QoIs relevant to the intended COU decision.",
      "rationale": "A thorough qualitative assessment was conducted by the modeling team in consultation with the device design engineer and the regulatory submission lead. The three QoIs — construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement — were identified as the primary mechanical performance indicators for pedicle screw construct integrity under the F1717 protocol. The clinical relevance mapping documented in the submission dossier confirms that stiffness governs load transfer to the vertebral body, yield force corresponds to the onset of permanent deformation that would compromise fixation, and force at 40 mm represents the ultimate load-bearing capacity under large displacement. The team concluded that these QoIs comprehensively capture the biomechanical behavior pertinent to the COU and that no additional QoIs are required for a medium-consequence, medium-influence classification. This determination was reviewed by an independent senior biomechanical engineer and accepted without modification."
    },
